{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> στίλβ-ω</b>, <br /> chiefly <i>present</i> and <i>imperfect</i>: <i>aorist</i> ἔστιλψα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Charito Scriptor Eroticus 2.2, 5th c.AD: Aristaenetus Rhetor 1.25 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<b>glitter, gleam</b>, of polished or bright surfaces, χιτῶνας.. ἦκα στίλβοντας ἐλαίῳ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.596; κάλλεΐ τε στίλβων καὶ εἵμασιν 3.392; κάλλεϊ καὶ χάρισι στίλβων 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.237 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; λαμπραὶ δ᾽ ἀκτῖνες ἀπ᾽ αὐτοῦ αἰγλῆεν στίλβουσι <b>beam</b> from him, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Hymni Homerici” 31.11; ὀμμάτων στίλβειν ἄτο.. φλόγα 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 17.55 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. ὅπλοις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 1146 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἰδὼν στίλβοντα τὰ λάβδα, i.e. the λ upon the Spartan shields, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 359; σ. νῶτον πτερύγοιν χρυσαῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 697; σ. ἄνθει.. ἐπωμίδας 5th c.BC: Achaeus Tragicus 4.3; σ. ἐν χρωμάτων ποικιλίᾳ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 110d, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Sensu” 77; ἱμάτια στίλβοντα NT.Mark.9.3: _absolutely_, of gold, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 59b \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]; of sleek horses, σ. ὥστε κύκνου πτερόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Rhesus” 618 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of brilliant complexion, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 2.79, etc. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; of water in motion, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 370a18 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of the white <b>gleam</b> on the eye, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “HA” 561a32, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 16.610; ὁρᾶν τῷ στίλβοντι 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Sensu” 26 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of fixed stars, opposed to planets (exc. Mercury, see at {στίλβων}), <b>twinkle</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Analytica Posteriora” 78a30, “Cael.” 290a18: c._accusative_ _cognate_, σ. ἀστραπάς\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] <b>flash</b> lightning, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 480: _metaphorically_, σ. ὁμηλικίην ἐρατεινήν 5th-6th c.AD: Orphica “Argonautica” 1115. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>shine, be bright</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 194 (_anapaest meter_). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>transitive</i>,= στιλπνόω, στίλβει πρόσωπον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 1.84 (variant for{στιλβοῖ}); στίλψασα τὰς παρειὰς ἐντρίμματι 5th c.AD: Aristaenetus Rhetor [same place] \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4744","accentedUnicode":"στίλβω","shortDef":"to dazzle, be radiant","mediumDef":"to dazzle, be radiant <br /><b>to shine, glisten, be radiant,</b> <ref='Mrk.9.3'>Mk. 9:3</ref>*","stepGloss":"to shine","stepTransliteration":"stilbō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"relucir, centellear, resplandecer","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 閃耀, 閃爍<br>   1a) 衣服的 (可 9:3)","_zh_Definition":"1) 闪耀, 闪烁<br>   1a) 衣服的 (可 9:3)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"sáng rực; lấp lánh","_zh_tw_Gloss":"光","_es_Gloss":"brillar","_zh_Gloss":"光"}]}